%% Protection Bundle Data Flow — Phase 1
%%
%% Architecture corrected per D31: OpenClaw IS the bot.
%% It makes outbound HTTPS calls to LLM providers.
%% The proxy intercepts on the outbound path.
%%
%% Phase 1 vault role: scan only, no key injection.
%% Vault injection is Phase 2.

sequenceDiagram
    participant OC as OpenClaw (bot)
    participant AP as aegis-proxy<br/>127.0.0.1:AEGIS_PORT
    participant SLM as SLM Hook
    participant EV as Evidence Recorder
    participant CV as Credential Vault
    participant WB as Write Barrier
    participant API as api.anthropic.com

    Note over OC,AP: OpenClaw config:<br/>baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:AEGIS_PORT

    OC->>AP: POST /v1/messages
    Note over AP: Check anthropic-version header (D31-A)
    alt Missing anthropic-version
        AP-->>OC: 422 provider_not_supported
    end

    AP->>AP: Parse Anthropic request body
    AP->>AP: Rate limit check (Ed25519 fingerprint, D30)

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over AP,CV: Pre-request middleware (skip in pass-through mode)
        AP->>EV: Record request receipt<br/>(method, path, body_hash, timestamp)
        AP->>WB: Check write barrier
        WB-->>AP: Allow / Warn / Block
        AP->>SLM: Screen messages[] + system<br/>(parsed content, not raw JSON)
        SLM-->>AP: Admit / Quarantine / Reject
        AP->>CV: Scan request for exposed credentials
        CV-->>AP: Clean / Detected(secrets)
    end

    AP->>API: Forward request<br/>(x-api-key passthrough, no vault injection in Phase 1)

    alt Content-Type: text/event-stream (SSE)
        API-->>AP: Streaming SSE chunks
        AP-->>OC: Forward each chunk immediately (no buffer)
        Note over AP: Evidence receipt for SSE:<br/>deferred until stream completes
    else Content-Type: application/json
        API-->>AP: Buffered JSON response

        rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
            Note over AP,CV: Post-response middleware
            AP->>EV: Record response receipt<br/>(status, body_hash, duration_ms)
            AP->>CV: Scan response for credential leakage
            CV-->>AP: Clean / Detected(secrets)
        end

        AP-->>OC: JSON response
    end
